'''Ağkənd''' (also, '''Spitakşen''' and '''Spitakshen''') is a village in the [[Khojavend Rayon]] of [[Azerbaijan]], de facto part of the [[Republic of Artsakh]]. The village's name means "white village" in both the [[Azerbaijani language]] and the [[Armenian language]].

