{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} The '''Bas Saharan Basin''' ({{Lang-ar|وادي بس صحران}}) is an [[artesian aquifer]] system which covers most of the [[Algeria]]n and [[Tunisia]]n [[Sahara]] and extends to [[Libya]], enclosing the whole of the [[Grand Erg Oriental]].
