{{Infobox feature on celestial object |name = Hun-Came Macula |image = [[File:Pluto-BrassKnuckles-20150716.jpg|frameless|250px]] |caption = The [[Brass Knuckles (Pluto)|Brass Knuckles]] chain of equatorial dark regions on [[Pluto]] |location = [[Pluto]] |coordinates= {{coord|10|S|20|W|globe:pluto_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |peak = |discoverer = |eponym = [[Jun Kameh]] }}
'''Hun-Came''' is one of the "[[Brass Knuckles (Pluto)|Brass Knuckles]]", a series of equatorial dark regions on [[Pluto]]. It is named after [[Jun Kameh]] {{IPA-myn|ˈχun kʰəˈmeh|}} "One Death", one of the [[Maya death gods#K'iche'|Quiché death gods]] in the [[Popol Vuh]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Chang|first1=Kenneth|title=NASA’s New Horizons Spacecraft Completes Flyby of Pluto|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/15/science/space/nasa-new-horizons-spacecraft-reaches-pluto.html|publisher=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=14 July 2015|date=14 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Rogers|first1=Adam|title=The New, Nerdy Mythology of Pluto's Place Names|url=https://www.wired.com/2015/07/new-nerdy-mythology-plutos-place-names/|publisher=Wired|accessdate=14 July 2015|date=14 July 2015}}</ref> [[File:PlutoMapFeatures-Updated-20150727a.jpg|thumb|[[Cthulhu (Pluto)|Cthulhu]] and the "Knuckles". Hun-Came is a small region at the far right, just east of [[Vucub-Came (Pluto)|Vucub-Came]].]]
