{{refimprove|date=June 2017}}{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2011}} {{Infobox settlement <!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions --> | name = Shushi | native_name = Շուշի | type = [[Administrative divisions of the Republic of Artsakh|Province]] | image_map = NKR locator Shushi.png | seat_type = Capital | seat = [[Shushi]] | leader_title = Governor | leader_name = Vladimir Kasyan | area_total_km2 = 383 | area_water_percent = Negligible | area_rank = [[Administrative divisions of the Republic of Artsakh#By_area|Ranked 7th]] | population_total = 5,599 | population_as_of = 2013 | population_rank = [[Administrative divisions of the Republic of Artsakh#By_population|Ranked 7th]] | population_density_km2 = auto | postal_code_type = | postal_code = AZ 5800 | area_code_type = [[FIPS 10-4]] | area_code = | iso_code = | website = [http://shusha-ih.gov.az Shushi Province] }} [[Image:Shushi tank memorial-DCP 3043.JPG|right|thumb|300px|The Shushi tank memorial]]
'''Shushi Province''' ({{lang-hy|Շուշի}}) is a [[Administrative divisions of the Republic of Artsakh|province]] of the ''de facto'' [[Republic of Artsakh]]. The Republic has [[Political status of Nagorno-Karabakh|limited international recognition]]. It is ''de jure'' part of the Republic of [[Azerbaijan]]. The province has 7 communities of which 1 is considered urban and 6 are rural.
== Sites of interest == * [[Shusha|Shushi]], its largest community. * "The rock" of Shushi, below which is the village of Karin Tak (Քարին Տակ; Under the Rock). "The rock" is historic in [[Armenia]]n history as it was from there that Armenian fighters ambushed the [[Azeri]] military who were held in Shushi during the [[Nagorno-Karabakh War]] * [[Ghazanchetsots Cathedral]], 1868–1887 * The Shushi Tank Memorial * The church of Kanatch Zham (Կանաչ Ժամ եկեղեցի), 1847<ref>''Artsakh: A Photographic Journey'' by Hrair Khatcherian, p. 12.</ref>
[[Image:Shushi-walls-P1003108.JPG|left|thumb|400px|Old city walls of Shushi.]] [[Image:Ghazanchetsots.jpg|left|thumb|400px|Ghazanchetsots Cathedral.]]
